2026-04-21 01:31:47 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['switch contacts in Control Module 3', 'internal series conductor of Control Module 3 (+ rail)'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that Control Modules 1 and 2 have a healthy 12 V across their rails and their indicators drop ~1.3 V, so they conduct correctly. At Control Module 3, however, the +12 V is present only on the input + cable (P-side), while the module’s output + rail and every downstream module remain at ~0 V, and all later LEDs are off. Cable continuity from the output of Module 3 to the load has been verified good, so the open circuit must be internal to Module 3, between its input + terminal and its output + terminal / switch circuit. This is consistent with either failed switch contacts (internally open despite being in the ON position) or a broken PCB trace/series conductor in the + rail of Control Module 3. Replacing/repairing that module’s switch/series conductor should restore +12 V to the downstream chain.'
